msgid "Vertex Group"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/tracking/track_to.rst:46
msgid ""
"When *Target* is a mesh, a new field is display where a vertex group can "
"be selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/tracking/track_to.rst:48
msgid "To"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/tracking/track_to.rst:48
msgid ""
"The tracking local axis, i.e. the owner's axis to point at the target. "
"The negative options force the relevant axis to point away from the "
"target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/tracking/track_to.rst:51
msgid "Up"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/tracking/track_to.rst:51
msgid ""
"The \"upward-most\" local axis, i.e. the owner's axis to be aligned (as "
"much as possible) with the global Z axis (or target Z axis, when the "
"*Target* button is enabled)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/tracking/track_to.rst:56
msgid "Target Z"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/tracking/track_to.rst:54
msgid ""
"By default, the owner's *Up* axis is (as much as possible) aligned with "
"the global Z axis, during the tracking rotations. When this button is "
"enabled, the *Up* axis will be (as much as possible) aligned with the "
"target's local Z axis?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/tracking/track_to.rst:59
msgid "Space"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/tracking/track_to.rst:59
msgid ""
"This constraint allows you to choose in which space to evaluate its "
"owner's and target's transform properties."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/rigging/constraints/tracking/track_to.rst:63
msgid ""
"If you choose the same axis for *To* and *Up*, the constraint will not be"
" functional anymore (red state)."
msgstr ""

